-- OAO Gazprom, Lukoil, Razgulay, Rosneft May Move: Russian Equity Preview
-- Anastasia Ustinova
-- 2010-07-05T02:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/oao-gazprom-lukoil-razgulay-rosneft-may-move-russian-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  
 Russia’s ruble-based  Micex Index  added 2.6 percent to
1,288.05 in Moscow. The dollar-denominated  RTS Index  rose 2.2
percent 1,316.65.  
 OAO Gazprom  (GAZP RX): The world’s biggest natural gas
producer is looking at assets in Russia and the Caspian region
held by BP Plc as the U.K. oil company moves ahead with a $10
billion sale of international businesses, the London-based
Times said, citing unidentified persons. Gazprom rose 3.3
percent to 147.99 rubles.  
 OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX): Copper prices rose the
most in a week after the U.S. unemployment rate declined, easing
economic concerns. Shares in Russia’s largest minter rose 3.2
percent to 4,503.21 rubles.  
 OAO Razgulay  (GRAZ RX): Raw sugar rose to a 10-week high on
speculation that Russian purchases will increase next month
after the nation lowered its import tax. The Russian sugar and
grain producer added 1.9 percent to 38.35 rubles  
 OAO Rosneft  (ROSN RX) and  OAO Lukoil  (LKOH RX): Crude oil
for August delivery fell 81 cents to $72.14 a barrel on the New
York Mercantile Exchange, the lowest settlement since June 8.
Rosneft, Russia’s largest oil producer, added 2.3 percent to
188.95 rubles. Lukoil, Russia’s biggest non-state oil company,
rose 2.1 percent to 1,585.63 rubles.  
